"What a Man" is a song written by Dave Crawford, and originally recorded for 
Stax Records' Volt imprint by Linda Lyndell, whose recording reached No. 50 on 
the Billboard R&B chart in 1968. As "Whatta Man", a version was recorded in 
1993, with greater commercial success, by Salt-n-Pepa with En Vogue.
